#
# Format: one fingerprint per line. Fingerprint format is:
#   <commit-sha>:<file>:<rule-id>:<line>
# Reproduce locally with:
#   docker run --rm -v "$PWD:/repo" --workdir /repo \
#     zricethezav/gitleaks:v8.30.0 detect --source=/repo --no-banner \
#     --report-format json --report-path /tmp/gitleaks.json
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# False positive: git checkpoint SHA in archived ADV task notes
#
# ADV archives include a `change.json` projection that records the per-task
# `checkpointSha` (a git commit SHA) and task `notes` that reference the same
# SHA prose. Gitleaks' `generic-api-key` rule classifies these 40-char hex
# strings as high-entropy secrets when they appear inside JSON string values.
# They are not secrets — they are public git commit SHAs visible in `git log`.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
